race.comment: SOME SECRET (1) has a strong record this trip including two wins from three starts. Scored by 1.5 lengths last time (16.97) in a T3 Grade 7 over 300m at this track. Looks the one to beat with even luck. KARACHI (4) was safely held last time finishing a 5.5 lengths fifth at this track (17.00) but back to the scene of his latest victory. Returns to favourable track. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Has ability and is one of the better chances. BERRINGA PADDY (8) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Ballarat over 390m behind Lektra Roger (22.69) in a T3 Grade 6. Was in the money prior to that. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Cannot be left out. MY COOL BREEZE (6) is fresh from a short break and ready to run well.
